{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"07458f14-4886-4d77-bea4-0986bb303bdf","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2, which supports constructor injection for `TestContext`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init (replaces [TestInitialize] for async work)\n    public Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test setup here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (replaces [TestCleanup] for async work)\n    public Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — MSTest 3.x injects `TestContext` automatically; no need for the property setter pattern.\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement this for async per-test setup (runs before each test).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — the async counterpart for teardown.\n- You can still combine these with `[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]` for one-time class-level setup.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3fa4f5e0-59e8-47a6-9832-d5c1a9defcb8","outputTokens":359,"requestId":"5819:21CC79:173E900:18B2C7A:6A0338AA"},"id":"1eeca811-0196-4ada-a57e-045340856db7","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:27:01.662Z","parentId":"3baa4c1f-ff6f-4c68-b381-2a36a7168852"}
